### Feature Description

Expose the `ComponentRef` of the component dialog is shown as a property of `MatDialogRef`:
```typescript
const {componentRef} = dialogRef
```

### Use Case

I have a custom helper that allows for seamless routing to dialogs, as if these were regular routes. Angular 16 added ["Passing router data as component inputs"](https://blog.angular.io/angular-v16-is-here-4d7a28ec680d#398f) that I really liked enough to update the dialog helper, achieving the same result. Unfortunately, the only way to grab a `ComponentRef` off `MatDialogRef` is with private API:
```typescript
const componentRef = dialogRef._containerInstance._portalOutlet.attachedRef;
const mirror = reflectComponentType(dialogComponent);
if (componentRef instanceof ComponentRef && mirror) {
  for (const { templateName } of mirror.inputs) {
    componentRef.setInput(templateName, injector.get(ActivatedRouteSnapshot).data[templateName]);
  }
}
```
